<refnamediv><refname>dnn_decode_segmentation</refname><refpurpose>Convert segmentation class-score tensors to a label mask.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>mask = dnn_decode_segmentation(output)
mask = dnn_decode_segmentation(output, layout)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>output :</term><listitem><para>Segmentation score tensor.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>layout :</term><listitem><para>Tensor layout: <literal>"auto"</literal>, <literal>"whc"</literal>, <literal>"hwc"</literal>, or <literal>"chw"</literal>. The default is <literal>"auto"</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>mask :</term><listitem><para>Label image whose value is the winning class index for each pixel.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>dnn_decode_segmentation</function> selects the highest scoring class for every pixel. Use the <literal>layout</literal> argument when the model output order is known; OpenCV Zoo PP-HumanSeg output from IPCV is commonly decoded as <literal>"whc"</literal>.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
scores = cat(3, [0.9 0.1; 0.1 0.2], [0.1 0.9; 0.8 0.7]);
mask = dnn_decode_segmentation(scores, "hwc");
]]></programlisting><programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
image = uint8(zeros(120, 160, 3));
mask = uint8(zeros(120, 160));
mask(30:90, 50:120) = 1;
imshow_segmentation(image, mask);
]]></programlisting></refsection>
